This paper discusses adversarial examples in machine learning, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields of computer science. However, given the focus on image datasets (CIFAR10 and MNIST) and the use of user studies to evaluate perceptual similarity, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses strategies for defending against adversarial examples, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of user studies to evaluate perceptual similarity suggests a focus on human-computer interaction, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
